@NODE "regger" "How to Register"
@TOC "MAIN"

                        Registering Buttonz
                        -------------------

Don't worry, it's not what you think. When I first started writing Buttonz
back in September of 1996 it was designed mainly for my own use as I'm not a
huge fan of menus and wanted to stop using ToolsDaemon, even though it's a
nice program there's no doubt. As I went through the early stages of creating
the program the features and nice-touches just kept going in until it was no
longer just a personal thing but something anyone and everyone could use if
they so wished.

And so: why shouldn't they?

Hence, Buttonz is given away as giftware. My way of saying "Thank you!" to
the Amiga community (which can not die no matter what the fuckwits in
companies like Escom and VisCorp do to us) which has given me so much in the
10 years that I've owned an Amiga.

If you like it then send me a gift, or an email. I ask no more. I may make the
source code available at a future date for other blitz users who find an 
interest in it.


                                @{"Contents Page" LINK "MAIN"}

